With the country now assured of a referendum, possibly by June this year, the ongoing debate over BBI will determine the future of the country.  And, by the look of things, it will be quite different from the Kenya many have grown up in. Latest salvo is aimed at the Thursday meeting between the President and opposition leaders. Candidates intensify the hunt for votes ahead of mini polls slated for March 4 in different parts of the country. Each member State will decide when and how to enter the trade pact known as the Economic Partnership Agreements (EPAs). Multibillion-shilling programme is aimed at boosting access to sanitation facilities in the city within five years.